just thinking out loud about my personal train of thought
summary: The thing about Caleb and Jester is that I do kinda ship it and on one hand the idea of outgrowing a crush and falling in love...
body:
The thing about Caleb and Jester is that I do kinda ship it and on one hand the idea of outgrowing a crush and falling in love with someone new is narratively fascinating… 

but the whole “girl stops being in love with the handsome guy she’s been pining over from the start and realizes she’s actually in love with the nerdy quiet dude that always liked her” trope has been used too often to shame women for being “shallow” and rewarding trope-y sad white males for their persistence

and I’m not saying that’s what it would be but my knee jerk reaction is I don’t trust like that.
